I'm no expert nor student of Anthropology, but I was impressed with this museum. Wow.  I learned a lot!
The displays and exhibits were nicely done. The building is very spacious with big windows. Very clean. This museum will take a while to go through, though. Plan to spend 2 hours or more, but it's worth the time. There is so much more than &quot;big stone heads.&quot;

A  quiet and peaceful place to spend several hours away from the hustle and bustle of the city, with the added bonus of coming away more knowledgeable and better informed.
